(3)

where git are gates that control skip-connections. Both f and h have a gating mechanism that takes git as input and forces the model to accumulatively forget about the longer term dependencies and focus
on the latest information. Since lt is an unobserved latent variable, We explain an approximation for git in the next section.

4 MODELING SYNTACTIC STRUCTURE

4.1 MODELING LOCAL STRUCTURE

