where Wc, bc are the kernel parameters. Wd and bd can be seen as another convolutional kernel with window size 1, convolved over hi's. Here the kernel window size L determines how far back into the history node ei can reach while computing its syntactic distance di. Thus we call it the look-back range. Note that, at time step t, we compute a temporary estimation of dt+1:

dt+1 = Sigmoid(Wdht + bd) From there we compute its corresponding t+1 and gt+1 for Eq. 3.

(12)

Convolving h and d on the whole sequence with length K yields a set of distances. For the tokens in the beginning of the sequence, we simply pad L - 1 zero vectors to the front of the sequence in order to get K - 1 outputs.

5 MODELING LANGUAGE

5.1 READING NETWORK
The Reading Network generate new hidden states considering on input xt, previous hidden states m0, ..., mt-1, and gates g0t , ..., gtt-1, as shown in Eq. 2. Similar to Long Short-Term MemoryNetwork (LSTMN) (Cheng et al., 2016), the Reading Network maintains two sets of vectors: a hidden tape Ht-1 = (ht-Nm , ..., ht-1), and a memory tape Ct-1 = (ct-L, ..., ct-1), where Nm is the upper bound for the memory span. The Reading Network captures the dependency relation by a modified attention mechanism: structured attention. At each step of recurrence, the model summarizes the previous recurrent states via the structured attention mechanism, then performs a normal LSTM update, with hidden and cell states output by the attention mechanism.

Structured Attention At each time step t, the read operation attentively links the current token to previous memories with a structured attention layer:

kt = Whht-1 + Wxxt

